{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbb88a99-58ff-4898-88ef-d25f776883cf","content":"Here are the issues I found in this `template.json`:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** — Required field for .NET templates. Add `\"identity\": \"...\"` at the top level.\n\n2. **`defaultValue` not in `choices`** (line 10) — `targetFramework` defaults to `\"net7.0\"`, but only `\"net8.0\"` and `\"net9.0\"` are valid choices.\n\n3. **Invalid `defaultValue` for int** (line 24) — `maxRetries` is `datatype: \"int\"` but its default is `\"abc\"` (not a number).\n\n4. **`enableLogging` default** (line 19) — For `datatype: \"bool\"`, the default should be `\"true\"`/`\"false\"`, not `\"yes\"`. Some template engines accept it, but `\"true\"` is canonical.\n\n5. **`computed1` missing `value`** (line 27) — Computed symbols require a `\"value\"` expression.\n\n6. **`generated1` missing `generator`** (line 30) — Generated symbols require a `\"generator\"` property (e.g., `\"guid\"`, `\"now\"`).\n\n7. **`postActions[0]` missing `actionId`** (line 35) — Post actions require an `\"actionId\"` GUID to identify which action to run (e.g., `\"210D431B-A78B-4D2F-B762-4ED3E3EA9025\"` for dotnet restore).\n\n8. **Missing `sourceName`** — Typically needed so the template engine knows what text to replace with the user's project name.\n\nThe most critical issues are **#2, #3, #5, #6, and #7** — these would cause runtime failures. Would you like me to fix them?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a05ba44-c9e8-4302-a5b1-8d04c70edb8c","outputTokens":434,"requestId":"A7F0:229C6C:159A51A:1836433:6A051FA9"},"id":"4ca42af0-6125-4f95-a78e-7ba05014be7e","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:04:52.580Z","parentId":"16b26edf-c040-42bd-b9cd-6165faf15e44"}
